{
  "text": "We used six real-world datasets in our experiments: 110 sequences from two different chromosomes of Arabidopsis thaliana (AT1 and AT5), 110 sequences from three human chromosome (HG1, HG10, HG21), and a set of 38 yeast genomes (yeast). Details of the datasets are shown in Table 8 . Human chromosomes have a very high sequence similarity among different individuals and excellent compression rates have been shown in the literature [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . We selected three distinct chromosomes to cover different lengths. Yeast genomes are the most dissimilar sequences in our dataset and compression rate is expected to be much worse than for Human chromosomes. The degree of similarity between Arabidopsis thaliana chromosomes is in between Human chromosomes and yeast genomes.",
